    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><ref refid="classDali_1_1OwnerContainer" kindref="compound">OwnerContainer</ref> is a vector which own heap-allocated objects. Unlike vector this will call delete on the stored pointers during destruction. For example, you can define a vector of heap-allocated Node objects: <programlisting><codeline><highlight class="keyword">typedef</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>OwnerContainer&lt;<sp/>Node*<sp/>&gt;<sp/>NodeContainer;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">NodeContainer<sp/>container;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">container.PushBack(<sp/></highlight><highlight class="keyword">new</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>Node()<sp/>);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>container<sp/>is<sp/>now<sp/>responsible<sp/>for<sp/>calling<sp/>delete<sp/>on<sp/>Node</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting> </para>
    </detaileddescription>
